reviews.text:
Hotel Scheuble is a very modern and cosy hotel in the centre of Zürich. Ideally located in the Niederdorf district, this hotel is very pleasant for any type of stay.
The staff is at the top of kindness, including in early morning when having breakfast (which by the way is great). The rooms are very modern, recently renovated, and have all the necessary equipment (except a bottle opener 😋). The bathroom is practically luxurious.
Only point to improve, the bed is not of the highest comfort.

Very cosy and modern hotel in a central location. Short walk to the restaurants, churches and shopping.
Friendly staff and tasty breakfast.

High standards, which I’d rather rate wit four than three hotel rating stars. Only downside might be the noisy street in the morning, but hey you get a great location in turn! So, summed up, it’s a great stay!
Extremely closw to the Hauptbahnhof and downtown area. Friendly staff, super clean rooms. 2 elevators help you with luggage and free waters available with plenty of towels.

Average for the high price we paid. We’ve stayed in several hotels in the Swiss cities and this one could have been better. Our room was right across from bars and was very noisy until early in the morning. The room is not sound proof. Our server at breakfast was very friendly though. Make sure to call and reserve a parking spot because parking is not guaranteed which was not clear when booking.

name: Bierhalle Wolf

reviews.text: Great atmosphere, kind people and personal, live music. For all generations.
Swiss/ German food with live music. It is not a place where I would go on my own but if I have friends visiting, it is fun to show them. Food is good.
Great place for lunch & splendid cordon bleu. Service is very polite.

It's a funny place. Too central and can be touristy but the food is descent and the people all too friendly! Go from Fri to Sun when they have live music from 5 pm.. it's usually too traditional and it's also a bit loud if you want to chat.

Hi 😊 I love the place. We went the in the morning for a coffee. I end up getting Spezli with cheese and crispy onions. Very nice. Later in afternoon we return for dinner. That's when we found out that is first day of October fest .... they had a live music, festive dinner, cheep beer. Sorry, no candles. Definitely going back.

Description: Bierhalle Wolf is a traditional Restaurant that serves Swiss and German Cuisine. It offers a true feeling of the world famous Oktoberfest all year round – from Friday to Sunday there is live music as well, featuring well known «Schlager», party tunes and folklore bands from Switzerland, Germany and Austria. Bierhalle Wolf is centrally located in the Old Town within walking distance of bus and tram stops as well as Zurich main train station.
Cuisine: German, Swiss, Bar, Pub, Central European, European

reviews.text: Great place to sit outside and try to eat what must be one of the world's largest schnitzels. I only wish they had a better selection of beer.
Good food and drinks + a friendly service. Well priced for Zurich. Unfortunately the bathrooms were pretty dirty.
jumbo cordon bleu and christmas beers was a great combination. food and drinks came quick and with friendly service.
They have great beer collection but no chips/fries to munch on.
If you love simple but good German style food

name: Chop-Stick Restaurant

reviews.text: Awesome food and good service. Ordered over eat.ch but due to a problem on the side of eat.ch it never got delivered but chopsticks was nice enough to stay available until we got our food past their opening times. Thank you!
Even better than some restaurants I tried in China. Highly recommended for everyone no matter you are Chinese or not!

Very nice Chinese food. Great menu selection. Been there many times.

Could be slightly noisy as this place is also popular with big companies of tourists from China (which is a great sign for the food quality) - but this is now a non-issue due to COVID affect on travel..
Super authentic Chinese food in Swiss high quality. Cosy and clean environment.
Been to a few times here and the Chinese food here is great with good portion.

Cuisine: Chinese, Asian, Vegetarian Friendly, Vegan Options

name: Kormasutra

reviews.text: Really, really delicious curry. We've only had takeaway, because of lockdown, but it's been so good and I can't wait to visit when they reopen. Every dish we ordered was full of flavour and really fresh.

Great food and very authentic.
We come here on a regular basis and its always delicious, also very nice interior and great location in the centre of Zurich.
Great choice of vegetarian dishes also and very friendly and attentive staff.

No nonsense, good cooking. All the dishes were prepared to a high quality, and I thoroughly enjoyed them all. The salad was especially good (served in a tasty, spicy sauce), and the mixed vegetable curry was a delight.

Vegan dishes aren't marked on the menu (an opportunity for improvement), but they were happy to adjust to suit nonetheless. Personally I'd reduce the salt in general across the dishes, but I appreciate it will be to most people's taste as served.

The service was absolutely faultless; I was welcomed and felt well attended to from the moment I walked in. I think this is a great option for Indian cuisine in Zurich.

BEST RESTAURANT EVER!

1000000% RECOMMENDED! Samy is a great guy and has very funny stories to tell! Very nice staff and huge portions for not that expensive!

GO TO THIS RESTAURANT!
Absolutely tremendous hospitality and worldly food. Best Indian Restaurant in Switzerland.

name: Walliser Keller "The SwissRestaurant"

reviews.text: Second spot with vegan fondue in the city I’m aware of. Their supplier is Vegusto, so if you’re a fan of the brand you will love it. They add their own seasoning so it’s not the thing you could probably easily recreate at home, therefore I recommend visiting this spot. I liked the very Swiss vibe of the place and the fact they have outdoor chairlifts adapted to tables and you can book them to have the full Swiss experience.

Super restaurant, friendly staff and exceptional Fondue Chinoise! The chocolate fondue dessert was also note worthy.

I really enjoyed my stay and I'll make sure to come back!

Please note that you need to book your table in advance: we had to book 1 week in advance since the place is always super busy, but trust me, it's really worth every penny!
Friendly staff - though extremely long wait for dessert. Had to leave - after waiting for 20 mins (and repeated requests about dessert - ice cream)

You walk in to the lovely smell of Swiss cheese 😊
Everything on the menu is all swiss, prices are not too extortionate for Zürich, except 6.5chf 0.5L water 😨😂
Best Fondue in Zurich, great service and definitely worth a trying!

Description: The Restaurant is open for our Hotelguests of Best Western Plus Hotel Zürcherhof. To us, "Swiss Alpine cuisine" means bringing a portion of the "Swiss mountains" to you at lunchtime or in the evening. The rustic cellar vault brings to mind a typical wine cellar in the vineyards of the Valais. We put the aroma of the Swiss Alps on your plates. The original cheese fondue comes to you in eight different variations, as dictated by Valais tastes. And when your meat is brought to you on a hot stone, you know it will be cooked exactly as you want it. Of course, our menu also includes the classics; "Bauernbratwurst" sausage with onion sauce, and – naturally – Zurich "Geschnetzeltes" (stir-fried veal) served with rosti. Taste Tinu's crispy chicken basket. It's tender and succulent, with a mild spicy flavour and very, very tasty! In summer, we also serve all these delights on our delightful terrace beside the pedestrian zone. Have we whetted your appetite? We look forward to seeing you!
Cuisine: Swiss, European, Central European, Vegetarian Friendly, Vegan Options, Gluten Free

name: Johanniter

reviews.text: Good food in a bustling pedestrian part of old town Zurich near the hauptbahnhof. Zurich style veal and the lamb fillet with fig foam was very good. The apple strudel and strawberry ice cream were both avoidable. Service was very good.

Yummy food, typical Swiss kitchen. Very generous portions for a fair price, which is very hard to find in Zurich. Service could be a tiny bit more friendly...but would absolutely recommend and will return again :)
Not enough waiters and only one competent woman of all. The kitchen did a better job before the COVID. Now they literally messed it up with a burned and dry cordon bleu and bad fries.
Nice variety of menu items. Quick service and friendly staff. Good for a quick bite to eat.
Love this place. Must try dish-Reclate.

Description: Traditional Swiss cuisine in the heart of the city of Zurich. From various locally brewed beers to fresh seasonal dishes, we offer you everything your heart desires in Johanniter. We are happy to organize individual events of all kinds for you just 5 minutes walk from Zurich main station.
Cuisine: Swiss, European, Central European, Vegetarian Friendly

name: Weinstube 1923

reviews.text: We will have a good memory of this beautiful evening in the wine tavern in 1923. We were warmly welcomed and served and have excellent vegetarian / vegan. No measly, avaricious portions; everyone received a beautifully prepared dinner plate. Hard to believe that such a courteous restaurant still exists today! We will be back.

This place is quite discrete from the street but behind the panelled door lies a cosy, warm and very inviting restaurant.

The staff are exceptionally friendly and more than happy to help advise you on your selection.

You are not hurried it is incredibly relaxed

The food... well.  We went for traditional Swiss food. And it was delicious.  All full to the brim yet craving more!

Definitely a place I’d frequent again
Traditional Swiss with a surprising number of vegetarian and even vegan options. The seasonal menus are wonderful.

NIce place to have some wine.  Food.. not so much.

Eddies Winestube is my fave.
Good local cuisine. There is a second restaurant that exclusively serves vegetarian dishes. Delicious!

Description: The world has changed tremendously in the last 100 years. But there are also time capsules that simply stay as they are. The "Weinstube 1923" is one of them. It exists since 1858 and is operated unchanged since 1923 by the family Nussbaumer. Lay the smartphone and the laptop aside and enjoy regional Swiss cuisine in a unique historic atmosphere. Welcome back in time!
Cuisine: Swiss, European, Vegetarian Friendly

Cute small raclette/fondue restaurant.
Good quality, try the all you can eat raclette if you are really hungry. Nice selection of Kirsch.
Cozy place to enjoy cheese.
It was so great! The food is amazing and so is the service. 10/10
Despite the name, this place is essentially known for its excellent cheese fondues. The restaurant is relatively small and always full in the evening so reservations are strongly recommended.

Great fondue, I would have enjoyed a bit more fondue honestly, I guess I am a big eater
Service was amazing

name: Holy Cow!

html_attributions: Holy Cow! Gourmet Burger Co. ZÜRICH ZÄHRINGERSTRASSE
Holy Cow! Gourmet Burger Co. ZÜRICH ZÄHRINGERSTRASSE

reviews.text: The price is not high, but the cheeseburger I had was definitely sunk in ketchup, that was the only flavour :(

Didn’t fall in love with the food.
A good fast food burger place, maybe too fast... our burgers and fries were ready in just a couple of minutes (not enough for the meat to be cooked on demand).
The ingredients are of good quality but not cooked to my taste. It was missing of a crunchy texture.
The chicken burger was dry. For me, the chicken in a burger should be deep fried and crispy, not simply pan seared.
Also, the bun is more like a bread than a burger-bun. It is also way too big, hence the impression that the burger is empty.
The price is fair
Pay attention to your order nr. and you'll be treated by fresh and tasty burgers -not to mention the chunky fries. Service is friendly too!
Nothing special. Bun was too dry. The meat quality wasn't good. Sauce was plain ketchup.
Food is good and portions are reasonable. Do not expect cheap price, after all it's Zurich

Description: Holy Cow! Is about fresh, nutritious, and tasty locally produced home made food that is cooked in front of your eyes and served to you in minutes in a fresh and fun environment. All burger ingredients are freshly prepared every day using only use the best locally sourced Swiss meat and vegetable products. Every single burger served is cooked to order. At this time we do not take reservations, however there is plenty of seating so come on by!

reviews.text: It’s a small pizzeria though the Pizza was very delicious and not so expensive. I recommend!
Very nice and clean restaurant. Had a good pasta
We liked the pasta a lot. A place accessible to the city center. The staff were friendly and nice with us.
A Small place with perfect and taste pasta and pizza...you must go there.....

Enjoyed the quick food we had here. Wasn't expecting much of it but we had a pizza and a pasta which tasted so good we had it again the next day. Doesn't seat many but has a few seats outside too. If you're looking for a quick bite on the old side then check this place out..

name: Enzian

reviews.text:
My worst food experience in Zürich, by far.

The Beef Burger was a disaster. Presentation is to be ashamed of, just a big empty plate with a Hamburger sitting lonely surrounded by nothing. Costs more than 20 franks, and you have to pay for the side dishes.

I did not even eat half of it. The meat is some kind of pressed beef, tasteless and without any sauce or gravy. The bread was soft and spongy. And it took 30 minutes to « cook » this.

Extremely disappointed. I have stomach pain right now as I am writing this.

I do not recommend this place.
Nice cafe.
The staff was nice, even didn't mind that we changed stuff from the menu. Really nice atmosphere. 10/10 would eat there again!
Food and ambience is good.
The food was great and so was the service

Description: Entdecke unser vielfältiges Angebot im Enzian «eat&art» Concept Store. Neben unserer veganen Bäckerei findest du in den ersten beiden Etagen eine moderne Auswahl an Pflanzen, Blumen und Design Objekten, die exklusive Modekollektion von Enzian sowie ausgewählte Secondhand Einzelstücke. Die Beauty Abteilung im 2. Stock verwöhnt dich mit Treatments unter der Verwendung hochwertiger Kosmetik Produkte. Alles made in Züri.

reviews.text:
The Italian restaurant is nice and the food is really delicious, however one of the waiters that served us was very rude and unfriendly! I was helping him with the plates and he got very upset and replied in a very rude way which is really annoying and not understandable and that disturbed my mood for the rest of the night.
The waitress however was nice.
One of the best pasta restaurants in town. The pasta with truffle sauce is very delicous. Everything is freshly made. Friendly atmosphere! To be highly recommended!

Always one of my favorites in Zurich. I am not a pasta fan and I only go for home-made pasta. Here you can find excellent home made pasta. Plus the service is very good and it is always a pleasure to be advised about food by Elena. Price and quality balance is very good. No matter how booked they are they gind a way to squeeze us somewhere when we pop up without reservation.
Food is delicious. Prices are average for Swiss restaurant standards +/- CHF 25 for one main course dish.

I had lunch there and really enjoyed the food. The weekly menu featured so many great options! I will be back to try some of the other dishes. The service was outstanding even though the place was very busy.

reviews.text:
We booked the restaurant for an apéro for our wedding. It was perfect: very delicious, fair price and super friendly and flexible staff. All our guests loved it.
I highly recommend.

Excellent friendly welcome and service, very varied and lovingly prepared breakfast buffet, homemade yogurt. A pleasure! Thank you very much. Lovely again. The hotel belonging to it can only be recommended, close to the city and very quiet, modern rooms with every comfort, including tea maker and fine, delicious teas to choose from :)
Good food and great service 👍
Central and yet in a quiet location, this small but fine restaurant offers a wonderful atmosphere, rounded off by the lovely and humorous hosts :)
Must have visited

name: Alexi's

reviews.text: Had a good time here. We took the seat at the sidewalk cafe. It was perfect weather in october. We had fondue. Delicious. It was a relaxing teatime break after wandering around the niederhoff area.

Really cool place. Nice drinks. Nice ambience. Nice music. Prices according to the Swiss income hehehe so it hurted me. I think it's a very good option to chill out a little bit while going between places and walking around.
Amazing cheesw Fondue, must try! The restaurant was small and booked out the first time we came but glad we could come back for lunch.
Lovely traditional Swiss food. Great customer services. Must try the hot slow cooking stones with steak and Vegs and chips.

We stopped here after looking around for something somewhat affordable and that had chicken or beef. My friend and I both ordered the hot stone chicken, which came beautifully presented with a side (i got salad, he got fries) and some veggies, and 3 tasty dipping sauces. We were confused and did not realize that we were supposed to cook the chicken ourselves (cut into it, saw it was raw, and quickly figured it out!). That ended up being a super fun way to end our last night of vacation. We sat outside, and it was lovely.

reviews.text: Good Spanish beer, carajillo and anis. Great staff.
Staff always have timeeeeeeee, take it easyyyyy, mañanaaaaa

We looked online, and found this tapas restaurant. We arrived without a booking, and received the last available table. The tapas are in glass display, and the staff explain what each tapas is. The prices are reasonable, and we shared 5 between the two of us, which was enough for both of us. The drinks are resonabily priced, and the athmosphere is as you can see on the pictures. The tapas are served with some bread and a mayo dip. All in all a good experience, friendly staff, not five star quality, but for Zurich still good

If you are in for Tapas and co. You will be happy here. The service is friendly and good.  Quite calm atmosphere. It is one place I believe you won't keep grumpy once you enter even if you are a naturally grumpy person. I don't know why. But definitely not because if the food. Maybe the aura. Happy people happy place. Who knows. Worth visiting.

This place was open late on a Sunday which was helpful. Of the seven dishes we ordered, the ones from the display case which were already prepared were very tasty. The chicken wings and calamari and others that came from the kitchen were obviously not made fresh, overheated a second time, and had a terrible texture. I would definitely stick to the charcuterie If you were ordering at this place. Overall not bad. The staff were really helpful even though they were closing up shortly after we left!

Got Pu-erh tea instead of Oolong. An egg in the rice instead of crab meat. But the food tastes good, quiet place.

name: Suan Long

reviews.text: The food was very sugary and the egg roll was dripping oil, not moist, but oil. Very disappointing. I wouldn't want to come here again.

It's not real Chinese food....the price v.s. quality is too low. Food is too oily and I have to say the oil is not high quality. Taste strange the fried rice. The service is not even good. absolutely not for Asian people or who want to eat real Chinese food or Asian food.
Was very happy with this restaurant the food was delicious. The menu has lots of options. The service was great, would definitely recommend if your looking for Asian food. This is located in old town
Absolutely delicious Xiao Long Bao, had 3 servings (total of 9 dumplings). Was a bit funny that they were served on 3 plates... Will go again.

This was my first time ordering from here. Pork is one of my favorite proteins and when I went in there it was a no brainer. I loved the fried pork dumplings the lady on the counter was very sweet. Pork in chilli thai style was average and I expected it to be more spicy but it was alright and the phad thai noodles was also okay but no complaints since the covid-19 restriction, all of the people are compelled to take takeaways so when I must have reached home that could also have an impact on the taste and I am sure the restaurant is trying really hard and their best to make good food and there is always room for improvement that's why the 4 stars.

reviews.text:
The best chicken fast food in town!! Chicken burger and wings are really really tasty!!
The team are kind and friendly. I would definitely order again from them.
Keep up the good work guys!!

Excellent London-Style fried chicken in the center of Zurich! I've had friend chicken around the globe and ZFC is the best I had in the continental Europe. Reasonable prices too and very friendly stuff.

Best fried chicken I've ever had tbh 😋 the zinger cheese burger is everything and the sauce are to die for real, when ever I think of chicken now I just want ZFC fried chicken period 😋 and the delivery was faster than I expected I love it 🥰 thank you I look forward for more tasty fried chicken from you guys.

Awesome 👌

This is my favorite fried chicken in Zürich. The owner and staff are very friendly and helpful. The halal chicken is prepared fresh every day. The food was prepared right after my order and was hot when I received it. The chicken and fries are delicious. Prices are really good for the quality you get. Especially for students the discounts are really attractive (only until 16:00 o’clock). I highly recommend this place, and will come more often in future.

Reminiscent of the Palestinian Chicken episode of Curb. Absolutely the best chicken in town! It’s far beyond the quality of what the famous namesake can deliver. This place has become a town favourite in no time for a reason. Excellent!

name: Spice Village

reviews.text:
Good food.
A lot of variety.  It is called ZFC now and the meals are really delicious.
Had Butter chicken and naan for lunch, very tasty. Staff was very friendly. Good hospitality.
Delicious Indian & Pakistani food. Place is not big. It’s clean. Staff were very friendly. Prices are reasonable. Location is good

The food served did not resemble the pictures at all. It did not taste good either. The naan seemed to be the frozen kind from the supermarket just heated slightly. Very tiny place and could not add the bill correctly.
Excellent hospitality with excellent taste for indians .The owner is so kind..i was keen to write review since long but was not able to find the restaurant link on google...

reviews.text: Beautiful setting, very good pasta, excellent wine. Pleasant moment.
In the heart of the old town a lovely old style restaurant. Italian food with lunch menu at a very good price. Thanks for the nice service, we'd love to come back.
The market is very beautiful in Niederdorf located, many great market stalls, varied food, good mix of stalls. PS. missed the part at the Rosenhof this year ...
Nice Christmas market. Small but nice!
I really like this little Christmas market. Great location at the Grossmünster. Many small stalls. There are also some churros.
Small but nice
Beautiful
Clean and comfortable room with a huge bed. The only down side was that the steel door did not keep out the late night sounds in the building very well.

This place is a total scam. To cut a long story short, I was waiting in front of a closed, dodgy-looking bar that was at the address of the "hotel". After half an hour no-one had shown up, I called, waited another 20 minutes until someone arrived to check me in. As I had already gotten suspicious by that point, I asked to see the room first. I was led to another address on the same street and was shown my room. The room appeared to be in a very poor state, not clean, mouldy shower, hairs on the bedding. It smelled strongly of a cheap room scent. I decided not to take the room, was told to phone the owner, talked to her, she was extremely unfriendly but tried to offer me another room which was more expensive but looked just as bad. I decided not to stay at this place. Overall a catastrophic business which doesn't deserve to be called a business.

My siblings and I booked this hostel for 1 night, we were in a foreign country not planning on staying longer than one night, as we were catching an early bus the next morning when we arrived at 10 PM we had no where to stay the night as when we arrived the owners were smoking and drinking in the front bar, not even at the desk and the booking that had been confirmed for us, was in-fact not confirmed. When we asked for accommodations they rudely removed us from the building and told us to call the police if we had any problems, not providing us with any place to stay, a way to another hostel/hotel and not even a simple apology. Upon reading other reviews, this hostel seems to be under numerous names, perhaps to cover this mistreatment. Please stay away from this place, you will be much happier elsewhere. DO NOT STAY HERE.

Little money for little accommodation.  Fair enough for a couple of nights and visit the city centre. I was with family: 2 little kids (1 and 3 years old). No elevator. Cleanings could be improved. Anyway the staff was very nice and kind with us. Great location. A bit noisy coz of the pubs surrounding the accommodation. Overall was fun

Very bad and disorganized. Their management is poor. They advertise their hostel saying Breakfast is included in the price. Their breakfast was so bad that it would have been  better if they didnt provide it at all. Some bathrooms doesn't have lock. No shower gel either. The rooms are tiny and crammed. After paying so much money I expected better.

name: Osteria Borgo

reviews.text: Go somewhere else. It’s just not worth the money. The homemade pastas are alright, but presentation and amount of sauce aren’t. 3.50 per person to drink tap water. Bread presentation is nice. Bruschetta didn’t come with basil, and was bare tomato’s and burrata, no flavour and bread also was basic for the 12chf price. Ravioli comes with 7 pieces and very little sauce. Also not worth the price. Tiramisu is tiny and days old the cream is nearly hard, definitely don’t do that. They need to do much better for a spot in the middle of Zurich. Server didn’t know crodino, San Bitter or bitters at an italian restaurant and she had no recommendations to give on the menu. Training of staff needs to improve. Dog cookie or water not given to our dog but the other table’s dog received one just to add icing on the cake. Hope these specific details can help to improve other guest’s experiences.

Taste of food was simply bad, we ordered pizza and pasta and we didn't like any of them.
Service was also rather slow given that there were not many people in the restaurant.
The best thing of the restaurant is the decoration, it's a beautiful place with charm.

Delicious bread to begin with. Nice style, nice waiters.
Good value for money
Ravioli Caprino are fantastic! Definitely worth a try here! Service is fast and super efficient. Great choice of a restaurant in the heart of Zurich.
Slowest service ever.  I've been waiting for my check since yesterday.  These waiters have mastered the art of not seeing people who are obviously desperate to leave.

name: MyVi's

reviews.text: Small place, but sanitary rules are respected in covid times. Food is neither special nor exceptionnal but tastes correct. Service and prices are also correct.
This is one of those restaurant experiences that if you are visiting or live here you would want to try once or twice. The food was so delicious
Really expensive and not good (especially the Pho, which should be the stamp meal!!) + you paying 2 CHF for a glass of tap water. Don’t go!

Having anticipated enjoying the two emblematic dishes of Vietnam - Pho and Summer Rolls - I was unfortunately quite disappointed. I’ve traveled to Vietnam and had incredible culinary experiences there, and even attended a short cooking course. Their flavours are exquisite, unique, and fresh. But none of this was apparent here.
Many of the vegetables were a bit old and a little brown (from oxidisation), the rolls were poorly made, with too much filling, no flavour, and they fell apart while trying to eat them. The chicken in the pho was inedible. None of the flavours were right, and no effort was made to use Vietnamese mint or limes, which are essential ingredients.
Could do a lot better.
A yummi restaurant. Thank you Lan! It was again delicious. My Fav: Beef Rolls in Senfblätter!
